The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Bond, Pollard in KKR radar
                                                                                                                       7                                      Bond, Pollard in KKR radar
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: The Kolkata Knight Riders (KKR) are likely to bid for only one foreign player during the auction in Mumbai on Tuesday. The management, however, remained tight-lipped about their preferred choice.         
	The Shah Rukh Khan co-owned franchise, which has 10 foreign players on their roster, will release only one player. With a purse of $750,000 available to each franchise, it is unlikely that the KKR will be able go all out.         
	According to unconfirmed reports, Australia captain Ricky Ponting is likely to be released by the KKR. Ponting, who played only four games without any success during IPL-I gave its second edition a miss in order to concentrate on the Ashes.         
	Ponting will not be available during the first phase of IPL-III, from March 12-31, as Australia would be touring New Zealand. For the same reason, Brendon McCullum too wont be available during the first phase. However McCullum is an important player in coach Dav Whatmore and skipper Sourav Gangulys scheme of things.         
	Some of the players who are in KKRs radar are latest T20 sensation Kieron Pollard of the West Indies, considered to be one of the biggest hitters in the game. He can also bowl handy medium pace.         
	West Indies pacer Kemar Roach and New Zealands Shane Bonds names will also be in the reckoning if the management plans to release an injured Mashrafe Mortaza.         
	Current list of KKRs foreign players:         
	Chris Gayle, Brad Hodge, David Hussey, Angelo Mathews, Brendon McCullum, Ajantha Mendis, Mashrafe Mortaza, Ricky Ponting, Charl Langeveldt, Owais Shah.                                                                                                                     
